          <avActivityHighlights>Wind slabs require caution.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>The strong wind will transport the new snow. Fresh and somewhat older wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant in some cases. They are barely recognisable because of the poor visibility. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain and at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; In very isolated cases avalanches can also be triggered in the old snowpack and reach large size.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>In some localities 10 to 20 cm of snow fell yesterday above approximately 1000 m. Little snow will fall in the late morning in some localities. &lt;br/&gt; Weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on steep west, north and east facing slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
