          <avActivityHighlights>The wind will be strong to storm force at times. Wind slabs represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>The sometimes strong wind will transport the fresh and old snow. As a consequence of the strong northwesterly wind, fresh snow drift accumulations will form in the course of the day. These will form in particular between approximately 2100 and 2500 m. &lt;br/&gt; The wind slabs are barely recognisable because of the poor visibility. They can be released even by a single winter sport participant. &lt;br/&gt; Caution is to be exercised in particular on slopes, and on wind-loaded slopes in particular above the tree line.</avActivityComment>
